# Presence Voice Chat

## Context

We need to add a high-performance voice chat and audio streaming system tied to our existing presence routes. This will enhance the interactive capabilities of the presence menu, allowing users to communicate via voice and listen to shared audio streams (e.g., music, podcasts).

## Goal

- Implement a voice chat system accessible from the presence menu.
- Add an "Enable Voice" toggle (similar to "Enable Slowmode") in the presence menu.
- Bind voice channels to the same routes as presences.
- Provide admin controls to mute users, kick users, or entirely disable voice chat for a specific route.
- Build a solid, high-performance Go backend package compatible with our WebSocket streams for low-latency audio routing.
- Integrate a global user volume control that scales all sounds sent to the user (allowing users to mute locally, distinct from admin muting). (already have the ui for it in header)
- Automatically attempt to connect and enable voice for all users when active on a presence route.
- Leave the backend and frontend architecture extensible for streaming other media types (music, podcasts).
- Build a neat, compact audio control and voice chat menu that emerges from the existing presence menu.
- Integrate a music picker/player (via uploads or a YouTube iframe) into the new compact audio menu.

## Non-Goals

- Full standalone voice communication app (this is strictly tied to presence routes).
- Video streaming (audio only for now).
- Complex DJ queueing systems (keep the music picker/player simple initially).

## Steps

1. **Architecture & Spec**: Design the Go backend WebSocket binary streaming architecture and protocol for audio data.
2. **Backend Core**: Implement WebSocket handlers for receiving and broadcasting audio streams per route.
3. **Backend Control**: Add admin actions (mute user, kick user, disable route voice) and integrate with WS/HTTP handlers.
4. **Backend Extensibility**: Ensure the streaming system handles general audio payloads (music, podcasts) alongside microphone input.
5. **Frontend UI**: Build the compact audio control and voice chat menu extending from the presence menu.
6. **Frontend Integration**: Implement WebRTC or WS-based microphone capture, encoding, and transmission.
7. **Frontend Playback**: Implement audio playback tied to a global user volume level.
8. **Frontend Media**: Add the music picker/player (upload support or YouTube iframe) to the audio control menu.
9. **Final Polish**: Tie the "Enable Voice" toggle, admin controls, and volume adjustments into the UI smoothly.

## Verification

- Validate high-performance, low-latency audio streaming among multiple clients on the same route.
- Verify admin controls correctly block audio from muted/kicked users and disable the feature when toggled off.
- Verify the global user volume correctly scales all incoming audio levels.
- Verify the music/youtube player renders and plays correctly within the compact menu.

